This paper deals with a logic for real-time systems, which is relevant to the fields of artificial intelligence and software engineering. The use of tableau methods suggests a focus on logic and proof theory, which is consistent with the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper mentions a syntactic restriction for timeline-based planning problems, which could be relevant to the subfield of Planning and Scheduling (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the complexity of the satisfiability problem, which is a common topic in the subfield of Programming Languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper's focus on verification and model checking suggests a connection to the subfield of Software Engineering (cs.SE), while the use of a novel proof technique may be of interest to researchers in Machine Learning (cs.LG).
